meanings.definition: Princoxes: plural noun, meaning young men who are impudent or saucy
meanings.sent1: The group of princoxes giggled loudly in the library, disrupting others.
meanings.sent2: The princoxes at the party were teasing each other playfully.
meanings.sent3: The princoxes thought it was funny to prank their teacher by hiding his chalk.
meanings.sent4: The princoxes' mischievous grins revealed their true nature.
meanings.sent5: The princoxes' bold behavior made them stand out in the crowd.

meanings.definition: Princoxes: verb, meaning to behave in a cheeky or impudent manner
meanings.sent1: He tends to princoxes around when he wants attention.
meanings.sent2: She always princoxes with her friends during lunch break.
meanings.sent3: The cat seemed to princoxes by knocking over the vase on purpose.
meanings.sent4: The wind princoxes through the trees, rustling the leaves.
meanings.sent5: The mischievous child princoxes around the house, causing chaos.
